posts.cooked:
So newish programmer here…

before reefscape our coach wanted us to program the robot from scratch. So far I got the swerve drive generated from phoenix tuner, built and deployed the code via usb type B. I also reconfigured the radio. The problem I have now is driver station wont connect over usb and our computer wont see the radio over wifi. we have a NI roborio and the status light stays solid green. any fixes?
If the radio isn’t showing up in the WiFi list…. I’d start there…

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: You say it won’t stay connected over USB… can you elaborate? Do you mean you’re unable to deploy code? Or code deployed successfully but the DriverStation app isn’t connecting? Or something else?
Also, make sure the driver station has the firewall disabled.
I got it to deploy and it seemed fine but now driver station cant connect to the robot at all, firewall is off, team number is correct (unless im forgetting to look somewhere)
